inn1.comm: excellent carry to Ramdin. Back of a length and kicks up outside off, left alone
shortish and angling away, hits Khawaja on the sticker of the bat, blocked to cover
veering into the pads/shading outside leg, neatly picked off to long leg

swing and bounce! Finch has nicked off for a duck. He inspects the pitch as he walks off. Good length and nibbles away a touch outside off, Holder's height means that he generates extra bounce. Finch has a weak waft, pressing forward at it, and edges it to lone slip. It actually popped off the shoulder of the bat to Benn. Big lift! He takes it just below his chest
extra lift again! Raps the glove. Angled in on a back of a length, awkwardly fended to leg
back of a length and outside off, Smith gets on top of the bounce as he drops it defensively towards point. Beautiful start from Holder
full and in the channel, Khawaja ushers it through to Ramdin
too full and straight, straying on the pads, flicked smartly to deep midwicket
off-stump half-volley, forward and driven to mid-on
overpitched and outside off, driven sweetly again, this time to the right of mid-off
144ks, good pace and bounce as well! Taylor runs in hard and hits the deck harder. Short on middle, blocked
Taylor now goes full, not a half volley, and outside off, teases Khawaja to drive. He has a leaden-footed flash at it and is beaten soundly
back of a length and comes in from outside off, Smith plants his front foot forward and then shoulders arms

A direct hit could have dismissed Khawaja! A brief communication breakdown. Full and swings in on off, Smith presses forward and dabs it in front of mid-on. Khawaja was ball-watching but makes it in the end, aided by Bravo's throw, which wasn't good enough
dug in short on off, keeps Khawaja back. Fended to the bowler
short again, Khawaja glances it off the hips behind square for one
full and angled in, a fumble at mid-off from Narine allows an easy pushed single
full enough outside off for the drive. Khawaja presses forward and drives to short extra cover
Smith shuffles across off even before Taylor delivers this full ball on off. He calmly drops it in front of his feet
and he shuffles across off again, this is pushed full on middle, flicked through midwicket. Smith wants two.... Khawaja settles with one

short and width outside off, the left-hander frees his arms and unleashes a firm cut. That was destined to go for four. Instead, Fletcher flings himself to his right and intercepts the ball with one hand at backward point. Great intent from WI this afternoon
full and outside off, Taylor induces the drive. The outside edge rolls down to third man

dipping full toss at the leg stump, Smith, having ventured across off, misses the glance. Hits the outside of the front leg, but this was clearly shaping down leg. Holder decides not to review the on-field call - not out
full and around off, stops on Khawaja and messes with his flick. He ends up chipping in the air to the left of KP at short midwicket
full and angled in, nice stride forward and Smith smothers any swing
full and aimed at off, check-flicked in front of short midwicket
stump-to-stump line, Khawaja comes forward and gently plays it back to Holder
Khawaja nips down the track, Holder is wary of it as he drags his length back and hits the splice of the bat
full and outside off, Khawaja uses the angle from Holder and runs it down to third man with soft hands
Smith steps across off to meet this short ball on off. Dabbed defensively to midwicket
alarming lift off the deck. Short angled in and kicks up at Khawaja. He hops and fends it to the off side. Din't see such disconcerting bounce in the previous game
Tayor errs in length, overpitches this outside off. Khawaja illustrates a wristy drive through the covers. The chase is on from backward point. Fletcher keeps it to three
full and straight in line, turned to square leg

short and width outside off, that's the first boundary of the innings. The left-hander reaches out and cuts through cover-point. Trickles away. The cutter went awry there. Khawaja waited and creamed it
good riposte from the bowler. Extra bounce, short and outside off, rears at Khawaja, fends it. These two batsmen have already taken a few blows on the glove
overpitched and outside off, eased through the cover region. Another three to cap the over
short and angling away, Holder doesn't hit the deck as hard as maybe Taylor does, but uses his height well. Fended onto the pitch
now much fuller on middle, drags the batsman forward into a defensive push
full and swerving away, dabbed down to third man
back of a length and just a shade outside off, offcutter, sticks in the surface. Smith waits patiently and pokes it to slip
nasty bouncer on the leg stump, 10ks higher than the previous ball, 137ks, Smith pondered a pull before belatedly bailing out and yanking his head out of the way
another cutter, sticks in the surface, impressive variations. Smith does not have enough pace to work with. He is also tucked up for room. He prods it into the pitch via an inside edge
straighter ball on off, Khawaja plays for the turn and drops an outside edge in front of lone slip
round-arm skiddy ball outside off, pushed towards point on the back foot

Khawaja uses his feet and wants to attack Narine. He held this back and got it to dip on middle, leaves Khawaja searching for the big shot over the leg side. He ends up skewing a leading edge over mid-off
short and straight on off, Smith hangs back and twirls it behind square on the leg side
flighted and breaks in a bit on off, Khawaja, having come forward, has time to go back and defend
full on the stumps, pushed down to long-off for one
short and angling away outside off, Khawaja swivels and ends up dragging a pull to the midwicket region
short extra cover throws himself to his left and stops this drive from Khawaja. Sharp work from KP. I stress again, WI's intent has been good today
full cutter, opens up Khawaja, he pokes an outside edge square on the off side
very full and outside off, Khawaja jabs his bat down and is beaten
back of a length, angled in, and finds extra bounce, brushing the glove! Khawaja inches forward and jabs it to leg, loosening the grip
leg-stump half-volley, and that's punished. Smith shuffles across and whips it away to the long leg boundary. You can't bowl there to any top-order batsman, let alone Smith
offbreak, curls away a bit. Khawaja hangs back and watches the ball beat the outside edge
short and on the hips, whipped through square leg
breaking down the leg side, tickled fine past the keeper. Wrong line again, this time to the right hander
lovely ofbreak from Narine, grips in the surface, and comes in, takes the front pad, clips Ramdin's gloves and dislodges the bails. Narine though he had the Australian captain
drifts in and kisses the pad, beating Smith
Smith skips out and does not quite meet the pitch for a drive. Instead, he takes it on the pad
driven down to mid-off from off stump. Good stride forward from Khawaja
Khawaja leans back and chops this back of a length ball on off to third man
full and outside off, Smith throws his hands at a drive. No feet movement. Toe-ends the slash through vacant first slip
full and angled in on off, Smith tips forward and covers up well
back of a length and just a shade outside off, Smith steps forward and bunts it gently to the cover region
short and angled in, not short enough to pose a threat. The batsman gets on top of the bounce and punches an easy single to long-on
tossed on off and dips, Smith bends forward to defend
shorter offbreak, pushed to left of KP at short midwicket
another offbreak, perfectly pitched around off, drifts in and catches the top of the pad
Narine sends down another offbreak, Smith reads the spin now, clipping it gently to square leg
Smith shuffles across and whips this length ball from off stump to midwicket
full on off, full enough for the sweep, even as Khawaja took his eyes off the paddle. Played fine to the right of Ramdin. Brathwaite chases in vain. The result is a four
another communication breakdown. Full and angled in, leading-edged to mid-off. Smith sets off and is near the middle of the pitch. The opener sends him back
eased to sweeper cover for a comfortable single
full and veering into the pads, clipped out to square leg
short and angled in on top of off, no room. Chopped down towards third man
Smith uses his feet, Carlos pulls his length back on off.Quietly patted to the leg side
fullish and on off stump, pushed back to the bowler. Tidy over
short and wide outside off from round the wicket, the cut flew to the right of Fletcher at backward point. He skipped back and smeared it to the boundary
short and angled in, this is picked away to deep square leg
keeps it short and outside off, Smith rises on top of the bounce, punching serenely to deep cover
dug in outside off, Khawaja jumps back and controls a pull to deep midwicket
full and angled in, pushed down to mid-on
off-stump full toss, happily whipped to the midwicket boundary. Taylor hasn't been consistent with his lengths today
full and angled in on off, clipped to midwicket
length ball on off, right in Khawaja's hitting range. No swing. He launches it over long-on for the first six of the match
KP dives full-length to his left from short extra cover and stops this drive from Khawaja. Sprawling save
Short and angled in, Khawaja uses his wrists and guides it towards long leg
Smith presses across off, this is short on leg, loose stuff. Smith pulls, having got inside the line, nay just helps it on its way for four
indipper on off, Smith defends and gets an inside edge that rolls on the pitch
back of a length and outside off, from round the wicket, slapped to cover-point region
full and straight, Smith had shuffled across, picking it away to deep midwicket
full and straight outside off, carved out to deep point
back of a length, angles it into the right hander. Head over the ball, defended back to Taylor
full and hurled at off stump, tapped back to Taylor on the front foot
full and curls in on off, Smith falls over slightly on the drive. He ends up wafting it towards the covers
some flight to start on off, Khawaja comes forward and offers a dead bat to defend
shorter on off and middle, clipped towards short fine leg. Some hesitation but a misfield allows the run
too much flight, too full, too easily defended
drags the length shorter on leg, allows Smith to go back and nudge towards square leg
a tad too full again and driven to long-on
superbly played. Just opens the face and guides the bat towards extra cover to get one. Exemplary use of the wrists on slow surfaces, although this isn't exactly slow
starts with a full straight delivery and tucked towards midwicket
full and wide outside off, driven to cover. Off the toe-end, not timing at all
properly timed off drive but he finds mid-off does Usman K. Maybe a tad too full on this surface
wrong shot choice. Shortish and wide outside off, Khawaja picked the length early and tries to pull but inside-edged onto his body for a run
better length. Shortish on off, punched to long-on from the crease. Nicely played
another fluent drive to mid-off but no run because the fielder is quick on it. Just getting a bit frustrated with his failure to find gaps in the last few overs
shortish and wide outside off, Smith goes back to punch to extra cover
good line, fuller but straight and Smith defends
shortish but straighter and Smith chops a cut to short third man. Some more miscommunication but no damage done
leg side-ish and clipped to midwicket
flat and straight, hit to midwicket off the back foot
prevents the maiden with a crisp drive to deep cover off the full delivery. Good batting, didn't get exasperated with the dot balls
worked off the straight line to deep square leg for a single
full and wide, scythed to deep point for the run to get his second his successive fifty. Good innings but a long way still to go
shortish length outside off, Smith eases back and then punches to long-on to get one
on-driven straight to the bowler, thereby sending Smith scurrying back into his crease
tucked easily off the hips to backward square leg and a fumble allows the second. Better from UK
squeezed off the outside edge to third man for one. Nice line, just outside that off stump
overpitched outside off, squirted to deep point
nice use of the feet, gets to the pitch of the flighted delivery and drills a drive to long-on
tossed up outside off, mis-timed to cover again.
turned, off the straight line, to midwicket
flicks this to deep midwicket, picked the length on that shortish delivery early
nice end. Another tight over. Flight outside off, pushed to point
honing in on that off bail, steered to short third man for one
a short pitched delivery outside off, Smith rocks back, rolls his wrists on the ball to pull to deep square leg
another nice glide off the open face to third man
punched from the crease to long-on. Smith finding the gaps nicely
short and wide, laced to deep point
back of a length on off, tight and nagging, defended back. Good over again
massive turn and rip into Khawaja, swerves back in to hit Khawaja on the pad in front of off. Maybe too high, a muted appeal
flicked away, with the turn, to midwicket
more flight and turn, well bowled. Outside off, Khawaja presses forward to defend
runs to the pitch to flick to deep midwicket this time
overpitched on middle, driven to long-on nicely
yorker on middle to finish. Jammed out to midwicket to end yet another tidy over
tossed up on off, the offbreak, flicked to midwicket
more turn on off, Smith defends from the front foot
uses his feet, runs to the pitch and then clips but finds midwicket. Good tight bowling
slightly shortish on off, and so Smith hangs back but nurdles to midwicket for another run
comes down again, flicks past short leg for a run. Relatively safe
nice end. Just one of the over. The offbreak on off is defended towards point
superb shot. Exemplary use of the feet, gets to the pitch, and then uses plenty of power in his wrists to flick over long-on. got so much power on that, and it clears the boundary easily
flat on middle and leg, defended
slightly shorter outside off, punched to cover
flatter on middle and leg, clipped to midwicket
tossed up, Smith comes to the pitch, drives back. Benn picks up, throws the stumps down as Smith makes his crease with a dive
six more. Slightly short, Smith picks the length early, rocks back and then muscles a pull over midwicket for six. Really good shot, made use of the lengths on both occasions
Khawaja this time. Runs flowing suddenly. Flight on off, Khawaja gets on one knee and then wallops the slog sweep over midwicket for a massive six
the exact same delivery. Flight on off, but Khawaja strides forward to defend this time
shortish and wide, slapped to deep cover
flight outside off, wristily flicked to long-on for a run
shortish, but comes back in. The carrom ball. Cut to point
slower and straighter, Khawaja rocks back and tucks this to midwicket to get one
steps out, gets to the pitch of the flight, and then drills a drive over the bowler's head. Even Pollard cannot get to it, great place to hit the ball
slower but dragged the length back after seeing Khawaja coming. Padded up, back up the pitch
the flat slider on off, Khawaja goes back to defend
six more. Runs flowing here. Great use of the feet again, got to the pitch and hit the ball over mid-off, against the spin. Aided by smothering the spin
flight on off, blocked
what happened there? Flat down leg, Khawaja goes back to pull but misses. Ramdin fails to get any glove on it, five free runs
flat on off to finish, defended
flight on off, more use of the feet to drive to long-on. Really good batting
short on off, Khawaja rocks back and swivel-pulls to deep midwicket. On the bounce to the fielder
flight outside off, defended
lots of flight on off, clipped to short mid-on. That fielder is forcing Smith to play with an angled bat
runs down and then whips the ball to deep midwicket
hit, into the off side, towards sweeper cover
strays down leg immediately and clipped to fine leg
good length on off, turned to square leg to get one
back of a length on off, Khawaja advances but clips to midwicket
short and wide outside off, slapped to the sweeper cover from the crease. Nice shot
full toss outside off, driven to deep cover for a couple. Holder is on two lengths it seems
an offcutter outside off to finish, Smith steers to third man with absolutely no movement of the feet
slower delivery to start, shocker. Clipped to fine leg.
another cutter on off, sooooo much time for Smith to just whip to square leg.
yet another slower delivery outside off but Khawaja is aware of the field and cuts between short third man and point for a couple
the fourth cutter in a row. Outside off and cut to point, so slow again. Providing no pace
wow, wide on the adjacent pitch as well. A full toss outside off goes wrong
another slower ball on off, full this time and a languid drive to long-off
the seventh slower ball of the over. Outside off and punched to long-on
fullish and wide, smeared into the off side for one
shortish length outside off, Khawaja rolls his wrists on it and keeps it down, smashes to deep midwicket
overpitched outside off, drilled to cover
slower delivery outside off, Smith drag-flicks to square leg
naughty full toss down leg, holder gets away with it as Smith whips to fine leg, gets just one for it
slower delivery outside off, glided off the open face to third man for one
slower cutter outside off, Khawaja fails to get bat on his attempted steer
another cutter outside off, extracts a bit of bounce, pushed to cover
steps out this time but Pollard bowls a wider cutter. Khawaja finds cover again. A bit of frustration building
slower and wide again, Khawaja badly mis-times a cut to cover. Four dot balls
drills a square drive off the fifth ball to prevent the maiden
slower and wide, scythed to short third man. No run. Good over
fullish on off, Smith comes down and drills a drive to mid-off. Times that beautifully but fails to find  the gap
whoa, a lot of bounce on that as Khawaja fails to connect with an attempted pull outside off
dabs one to point.Smith comes down for one but is sent back late, a direct hit would have had Smith
he gets one this time. A short delivery on off, Khawaja comes down and toe-ends this past the bowler for a run
a slower delivery on off, Smith goes back and tries to pull but the ball holds up in the pitch and he fails to make contact. Off the toe end for a run
whew, that offcutter has jagged and moves away prodigiously. Beats Khawaja's bat by a distance. Ripper, opened him up completely
would have been out with a direct hit again. Full down leg, pulled to short fine leg where Benn fields well and fires a throw to the batsman's end but misses
cut to deep point
another cutter on off and middle, Smith looks to flick but gets a thick inside edge into his pad
short and wide outside off, and very slow. Toe-ended to midwicket.
shortish and wide again, mis-timed to long-off. Just one this time
a slower delivery on the pads, worked away to square leg for one.

taken! Smith goes. Superb bowling previously has led to a wicket for Brathwaite. A legcutter this time, quite full and wide outside off. Smith looks to execute an ugly drag-sweep into the leg side but the ball is top-edged and goes straight in the air. Hangs there for quite awhile, Brathwaite calls, settles himself under it and takes a good catch, hands reverse-cupped
very full at off, Bailey strides forward and push-drives it to mid-off
little offcutter on off, 109ks, Bailey waits and defends it to the off side
short and wide outside off, Bailey misses out, cutting straight to backward point
fuller and outside off, Bailey is forward as he jabs to backward point

back of a length and outside off, does not quite come onto the new batsman. He shapes to cut and ends up chopping to the right of Ramdin. Oh, Ramdin took his right glove off and crashed awkwardly on his right shoulder while looking to throw. He fails to effect a direct hit, Khawaja is home
offbreak, drifts down leg, Bailey prods and misses. And Fletcher stops it between the legs. Ah, not a wide!
pushed back to the bowler as this was full on the stumps
dragged down short and outside off, chopped to the covers on the back foot. Holder makes a diving save to his left at short extra cover
dropped short on off, Khawaja swivel-pulls to deep midwicket. One slip in, btw
offbreak, drifts in and catches the pad as Bailey wafts and misses. It was nipping down leg
reverts to the short length, swatted from off stump to deep midwicket
loopy cutter on off, dabbed back on the front foot
back of a length and outside off, jabbed out to Big Benn who has replaced Holder at short extra cover
Bailey skips back to cut this short ball from outside off to sweeper cover
another short one outside off, pulled with control to deep midwicket
Bailey steps out and gets a short ball on middle and leg. He adjusts and flicks behind square
roller on the pads, full in length, clipped to deep midwicket
offbreak leaves the left-hander outside off, short in length, and that allows Khawaja to rock back and cut to deep point
flighted, hint of turn on off, flicked to midwicket
skids off the deck, quicker and flatter on off, on the back foot is Bailey, jabbing to deep midwicket
shorter offbreak outside off, whipped nicely through square leg now
flat offbreak, forced to long-on on the back foot. Easy single
slider on off, Khawaja punches a single to long-off and keeps strike
fuller and spins in, inside edged onto the pad
slanted full down leg, wide
short and extra bounce outside off, chopped to point
similar ball, no room, chopped to point again

very full and spins in at the leg stump, quicker one at 102.2ks, tickled to short fine leg. Given as a run by ump Illingworth. Even if that was pad first, it looked like it was nipping down leg. Benn insists on a review. Holder calls for it. It is a legal ball. Projections show it has heading down leg by some distance
Bailey has ample time to rock back and lash this short ball outside off to sweeper cover
another fizzer on the pads, this is turned to short fine leg
short cutter on off, stabbed to backward point
full roller on middle, nurdled to short fine leg. They push for a quick single, Bailey wanted it. Benn fumbled while loading up for the throw
Bailey shuffles across the off stump and whips it away sqaure of short fine leg
dug in outside off, flat-batted away to short extra cover. Not middled
offcutter on middle, worked to backward square leg. Two men behind square there with Pollard dishing out these slower ones
length on middle, Khawaja aims for a wild, big heave across the line. Nervous 90s? He's been there for a while now. The gallery shot does not come off. He top-edges it into his helmet
drifts in on off and rips away outside off with extra bounce, past the prodding bat. Crackin' ball. That should excite Zampa
milked down to long-off as this was too full on the stumps
floated and outside off, down the track and driven to long-off
short and curls in with extra bounce, fended tentatively to the leg side

Bailey employs the reverse sweep and sends it past lone slip. It trickles away to third man.... Taylor dishes in the chase, and fires a flat throw to the stand-in keeper. Fletcher did well to gather the ball and break the stumps. The left-hander is short on the third. Khawaja falls two short of a century. His running had been tentative throughout his stay. Khawaja called for the three, he perhaps needed a full-length dive
drifts in full on off, dead-batted on the front foot
Bailey aims another reverse sweep, this is hit to deep point
offbreak, clips the thigh and runs fine on the leg side
short and quick, forced down the ground
offbreak, kisses the pad
down the track, meets the pitch, and pushes to long-on
offbreak, wafted to the leg side
punched to short extra cover
full and drifts in on off, Bailey leans forward and works it to the short midwicket region. A stiff-looking Benn gets to the ball
drifts in, overpitched on off, driven smoothly to long-off
superb connection. First boundary since the 27th over. Down the track and lifted over long-off. Clean strike
angled in and turns away viciously past the outside edge
shorter and turns away outside off, chopped to deep cover
Bailey nimbly skips out to meet this full ball, which is whipped over midwicket
short offbreak on off, the batsman hangs back and forces a single to long-on
floated on off, dabbed to the cover region from the crease
flat on middle and leg, Marsh is camping back.... might not be the best ploy. Turned to square leg
tucked through midwicket for one
short and turns in, on the back foot and punched to long-on. Australia have played out Narine without giving a wicket to the offspinner
full at off, driven to long-off on the front foot
short and outside off, cracked away to the off-side sweeper
full and just outside off, induces an outside edge that beats a diving Ramdin. Good ball straightened off the surface a touch
full on off, whippy drive to long-off
short cutter outside off, Bailey waits patiently and flays a cut fine of backward point
banged outside off, tennis-style swing to wide long-on. Forehanded it away
Bailey jumps outside leg, Holder digs it short on middle from over the wicket. Miscued behind square
full and speared down leg, wide
length ball on off, smeared down the ground, beats long-on's dive to his left. Taylor lets it away for four. Din't even get the hand to it
full and down leg again, why is that not a wide, Mr. Brathwaite? Marsh has a wry smile
skiddy short ball on middle and leg, which is jabbed to midwicket
rising short ball outside off, Bailey has to rise with it. Slashing a cut over a leaping Narine at backward point. He stretched one hand out but could only tip it over
length ball on middle, clubbed to deep square leg
Bailey skips out and nearly yorks himself. Whipped to leg
loopy offcutter on off, shovelled down to wide long-on
another cutter, fuller in length on off, Bailey crouches and wades into it. Smashing it over midwicket. He hit the pants off that
full at speared at off, dragged to long-on
low full toss on off, Marsh gives it away. The bat twisted in his hands and he ends up slicing it into the hands of Holder at mid-off
full and straight from round the stumps, whipped to long-on
back of a length incutter, Bailey slogs early to the leg side as the ball bounces over middle and leg stumps
Bailey moves outside leg, Pollard stalks him with a short ball. Pulled to deep square leg
leg-stump short ball, Head stays back and guides a single to square leg, his first run in ODIs
Bailey skips outside leg again, this is a short ball following him. Glanced to fine leg and Bailey raises his half-century. A busy one, that

Head skies this offcutter to the keeper. Ramdin settles under it comfortably. Full and leaves the left-hander outside off. Head winds up for a roundhouse swipe. He watches the top edge lodge in the gloves of Ramdin
floated full and slow on off, 98ks, nudged to midwicket for one
full and outside off, wider, Bailey reaches out, topples over, skewering a drive through the covers
Wade dances down the track, Holder shortens his length outside off and slogs to midwicket
wide yorker, Bailey reaches out again, but can't slice it away with an angled bat
full and outside off, Bailey slams it to long-off
short, possibly a slower ball outside off, it does not perturb Wade. He shifts his balance to the back foot and pulls to the midwicket boundary

The middle stump is floored. Holder pumps his fist. Wade cleared his front leg and shimmied out for a drill down the ground. This yorker shatters the middle stump. No cameo from Wade. Holder caps his spell with a wicket
Bailey jumps a long way outside leg and is chased by KP. Swung over square leg

Another wicket for KP. He is pumped. Bailey jumps outside leg again. Pollard sends in an offcutter chasing the batsman. He shapes to pull and ends up top-edging it to the short midwicket region. Ramdin with the big gloves calls for the catch and completes it
Faulkner is moving outside leg as well, back of a length and into the moving batsman, slapped to wide long-off
cutter outside leg following the moving batsman, worked to square leg
lobs a full slower ball on off, checks his drive and chips to cover
full and heads down leg, Pollard floated it wider as Faulkner backed away
slower full ball on middle, pushed through midwicket for two. One short, says ump Brathwaite. Tight call, seems. Was there a tickle behind the line? I think there was some bat there

inn2.comm: nice start. Fullish and wide outside off, solidly driven to mid-off. Not much movement
full and straight this time. Again, intentionally bowled fuller to try and invite some swing, but there is none. Driven to mid-on
full and wide this time, gets some away movement which was responsible for the ball going over Charles' flashing blade
ooh, full and straight. Out without a big inside edge onto pad
full on middle and leg, clipped towards fine leg. More off the inside half. A couple for Charles
shot! Overpitched and smashed. Outside off, Charles just drills a drive past the bowler, whistles to the long-off boundary
beauty to start, 132 kph. A good length on off and plenty of away seam movement takes the ball past Fletcher's outside edge
hesitation but no run. Back of a length on off, Fletcher plays it well. Gets on top of it and plays it down towards square leg
smashed. WI have come out with positive intent. Full and wide outside off, Fletcher backs away slightly and smashes the ball over mid-off. Did not bother keeping it down

dropped.  Should have been taken. Not good from Khawaja. Fullish on off, may have come back in slightly which was responsible for the ball taking the inside half of Fletcher's bat. Straight to mid-on, low but should have been taken
errs in line and gets punished. Short down leg, Charles pulls and it races away to the fine leg fence. Just got some bat on it
looks for the yorker, misses and gets punished again. WI on a rampage here. Strays in line, down leg and Charles calmly flicks to the square leg fence
nice delivery. Full and straight, a bit of inward movement. Fletcher defends
whoa. Not a bad delivery at all. Full on off, but Fletcher backs away, clears his front foot and mows this over midwicket. An ugly hoick but who cares? Just clears the boundary. Hmm
adjusts his length with a good-length delivery on off, tapped towards slip. Charles wants one, Fletcher doesn't
four more. Short and wide, poor ball. Fletcher gets on top of the ball and scythes a cut through point for another boundary.
full down leg, another poor delivery. Fletcher misses his flick this time as the ball pings off the pad
good finish. Back of a length on off, Fletcher stays in his crease to defend
fullish on middle and leg, pushed to a deep mid-off for one. Good batting, clever
full on off, a solid block to cover
phew, that was close. Fullish on off and middle, the ball comes back and Fletcher misses a flick. That looked out to me. Maybe a bit high? Australia don't even consider a review
lazy drive, full and wide outside off, a bunt past cover. No feet movement at all
way over fine leg. Six more. What a start this is. Short on off, the ball climbs high enough to take the top edge of Charles's bat. Flies over fine leg
turned away to square leg off the leg side-ish line
chipped into the midwicket area. Plenty of balls just lobbed in the air. Back of a length on middle and leg, Charles tries to nudge but gets a leading edge
another big swing. Fullish outside off, some definite inward movement. Takes the ball past Fletcher's swing. Just beats the stumps
better from Fletcher. Back of a length on middle and leg, nudged to fine leg
another loose delivery. Short on middle, Charles rolls his wrists on that and keeps it down. Gets the ball past short fine leg for three
that nagging line Hazlewood is known for. Good length on off, blocked
good finish. Back of a length on off, defended
dropped again. Much tougher chance, hardly even carried. Just about. Full on off, a lazy drive back to the bowler. In fact, lands just short
fuller than a good length on middle and leg, skewed off the inside half towards square leg. Again, looking for a big hit
good. Full on off, nagging lines. Defended to cover
back of a length outside off, Fletcher tries to open the face to guide to third man but fails to execute. Chops back to the keeper
six more. Runs coming all too easily. Quite full on off, Fletcher comes down with a lot of intent and pummels the drive straight back over the bowler. Six easy runs
fullish on middle, patted to point. Dot
full on middle and leg, very full. JC jams this one into his foot and back to the bowler
short and wide, poor delivery. Extra bounce takes the ball over the bat
pulled into the midwicket area. No one there so square leg has to run around to get it. In the meantime, the batsmen make two
smashed for four more. Sensational batting. Overpitched on off, Charles hammers it back past the bowler. Four more
driven into the cover area
shortish on off, pulled to deep square leg for a run. Played that along the ground
full and wide outside off, Charles drives but finds extra cover

Khawaja messes it up again. He is having a shocking day in the field. This was much easier than the previous one. Fullish on off, Charles backs away and heaves one to long-on. Khawaja comes forward, misjudges it and the ball goes over his head. Poor.
clipped to deep square leg
full on off, good lines. Defended
good length delivery on off, tapped off to third man. No run
another defensive stroke to end.  Back of a length on off, defended towards gully
tossed up, short and slow on leg. Easily worked to deep midwicket
short and slow yet again, easily nudged to short fine leg
flat and wide outside off, defended into the off side
back of a length on off, punched to long-on. Nice batting this
full and wide, hardly any turn. Goes past the outside edge
slashed over point for another boundary. Tossed up but too wide, allows Fletcher to open up his arms. Over point and that will be four more
back of a length outside off, tapped to point
good length on middle, blocked by Charles
poor delivery. Four more. Shorter delivery on leg stump, an easy offering for Charles who flicks past short fine leg
drifts down leg, slower ball. Off the pad to fine leg for one

gone this time. The slower delivery and Australia have their first. A slow, good-length delivery outside off, the ball stops on Fletcher who checks his stroke. Since he withdraws very late, the ball bobs up off the withdrawing bat and is easily taken by point. Will that spark something?
full and wide outside off, left alone by Bravo
seam-up outside off, the ball bounces extra and over the bat of Charles who wanted to dab one to third man
short and wide, another poor delivery. Cut away to deep point with lots of ease
shortish and wide, Bravo opens the bat face to guide to third man
good length and straight, shovelled to midwicket
punched to long-on
full and straight on off, Bravo defends from the crease
fullish on off, punched to deep cover
nicely played. Full and wide outside off, Bravo leans on the drive and times it beautifully. The ball races away through cover for four. just timing
driven to cover this time
fullish down leg, drifting down. Worked to square leg, Zampa puts in a dive
full on off, a thick inside edge onto the pad. Looked to go over the infield on that occasion
drifts down leg, and Bravo works this off his hips to square leg for a single
good length on off, Bravo stands tall to defend under his eyes
shortish and wide, Bravo looks to rasp a cut but misses. Cross seam, takes the ball over the bat, extra bounce
back of a length outside off, played down to point
short and wide, stops in the surface and Bravo is through his slap. Patted back
back of a length outside off, punched into the off side
short of a length outside off, pushed to deep cover
some flight on off, but no turn. Bravo comes down to defend
more flight on leg, punched to long-on, good use of the wrists to find the gap

flat and gone! Skids on with the arm and goes through Charles. Poor shot. Zampa lands it perfectly, a flat, slider which skids off the pitch and strikes Charles in front. Charles played back and missed a straight ball, absolutely plumb
more flight outside off, Samuels strides forward to defend
shortish and wide-ish, punched into the cover region
shortish on off, Samuels defends under his eyes
full on off, pushed back to the bowler
steered to third man off the back foot
drifts down leg side and Bravo works one to fine leg to get one
full and wide outside off, Samuels leaves comfortably
127 kph, full and wide delivery to finish. Too wide to draw a stroke and Samuels chooses to leave
too much flight and pummeled. Tossed up but too full, Bravo clobbers a straight drive past his partner and he gets four
slightly leg side-ish this time, Bravo was shaping to sweep but bailed out late. Flicks to square leg
too much flight again and smashed. Bravo leans on the drive and muscles it over long-on, didn't bother keeping that down. Clears the boundary easily
pats one towards point to get one
flight on middle and leg, Samuels comes forward to defend
defended again, flatter this time on leg, played away towards midwicket

crisply driven for four. Overpitched outside off and Bravo leans on the drive, gets it past cover. Marsh runs across but parries it onto his other hand while in contact with the boundary so that will be four more
shortish and wide outside off, Bravo hangs back and taps to point
overly full, overly wide. Left alone and a wide is called.
back of a length outside off, the ball moves away late and the ball beats the bat. Bravo may have played inside the line of that
full and wide outside off, Bravo lets this one go
full and wide outside off, Bravo doesn't bother with this as he lets it go
another leave from a wide delivery outside off
length and angled in from over the wicket, Samuels camps back and defends it to short extra cover
shortish and outside off, Samuels plays with soft hands, dabbing to backward point
pretty full and outside off, Samuels leans forward and caresses a single to sweeper cover. Driven neatly
full and angled into the left-hander from round the stumps, Bravo keeps back and drops it defensively in front of his feet
too full and outside off, Bravo has a leaden-footed flash and sends an outside edge flying... does not carry to Khawaja at third man
back of a length on off, Samuels blocks it to short midwicket to finish the over
full and aimed at off, Bravo glides a single to third man
Samuels leans back and jabs this short ball from outside off to backward point. Jabbing punch straight to the fielder
full and on the stumps, slapped fiercely to short extra cover, it bounces and bursts through the hands of Bailey at short extra cover. Mid-off has it covered
back of a length and tucks up the right hander for room. Played towards point
the bowler goes wide of the crease and angles this full ball in on middle, nudged to mid-on
full and straight, Bravo hangs back and picks it away through square leg
back of a length and outside off, punched out to sweeper cover
back of a length and outside off, Samuels stands tall as he eases it to sweeper cover
full and aimed at off, open-faced dab to point
full and outside off, steered down to third man for one
full and might have been a cutter, Samuels yanks his bottom hand off the bat. Loosening the grip and nurdling a single towards square leg
worked off the pads to short midwicket
sliding across off from round the stumps, slapped past diving short extra cover for a couple. The fielder dived to his left and took some pace off the ball
full and Head finds a bit of turn to beat the straight-bat push and rap the pad
jabbed to mid-off for one. Samuels is home, despite a direct hit from Finch
Head lands this just outside off, grips and turns past the prodding bat
drifts in full on off, Bravo thrusts his bat in front of the pad and blocks towards cover
turn and dip! Bravo aims for a leg-side flick and drops a leading edge in front of midwicket. Probing over
full and on middle, Samuels nudges it in front of short extra cover and sets off for a quick single
length ball angled in on off, Bravo opens the face and steers it past backward point to third man
leg-stump half-volley, flicked to long leg
too full on middle, driven down to long-off
heave-ho! Length ball on off, slower at 110.7ks, Samuels plants his front leg forward, waits, and launches it over long-on  for his 100th ODI six
chopped from the stumps to third man
blockhole ball on off, squeezed to sweeper cover
full and straightens on middle and leg, blocked
flat and quick on middle, bunted to the covers
floater on middle, milked down to long-off with a straight bat
Head twirls it full on off even as the batsman steps out. Driven to mid-off
back of a length and breaks in to ping the thigh. Samuels was surprised by the turn as well as bounce. He was left beaten
full at the legs from over the wicket, knocked to the midwicket region
short and zings outside off, the extra bounce foils the attempted slash. Bounces past the top edge
Samuels suceeds in slashing a single to sweeper cover as this was short and offered width
length ball on middle, helped to short third man off the face
full and drifting down leg, may have brushed the pad on its way to Wade. There was no deflection, there. Plenty of debatable umpiring calls this series
full on middle, invites the drive, hit to left of mid-off
full on middle, blocked
offbreak, Samuels jumps out, swings and squirts an inside edge onto the pad
skips out to a offbreak, inside edge does not carry to short leg
overpitched on middle, drilled to short extra cover
breaking down leg, diverted fine on the leg side
dragged short and turns away outside off, slashes a cut through backward point on the back foot
short on off, leans back and chops past backward point
short and outside off, cuts and misses. No feet movement there
full on middle, pushes with an angled bat to the covers
full and nips away off the deck. Beats the angled bat outside off to the keeper
Hazlewood pulls his length back on middle and pushes Bravo further back. He drops it in front of his feet
full and swerves away outside off, Bravo is desperate to run down to third man with an angled bat. Beaten again
spinning into middle and leg, blocked to short leg
Samuels skips out and aims to put the bowler off. He manufactures a half-volley and drills a drive past the covers. Nimble footwork
Samuels dances out again, this one spins and takes the pad. He wasn't quite close to the pitch of that ball
tucked off the pads to short fine leg, the fielder fumbles and paves the way for an easy single
full and outside off, big stride forward as Samuels carves a drive behind point

Samuels steps out and nearly pops a return catch. Offbreak, grips in the surface. Samuels is not close to the pitch again, checks his shot, and lobs it.... Head dives but the ball dips agonosingly in front of him
back of a length on middle, run away to backward point
full on middle, angled towards backward point for one, played it to the left of the fielder
short and angled in on middle, blocked quietly off the back foot
overpitched on middle, (reverse)swings in, clears his front leg, and drags to mid-on
overpitched on middle, Samuels replies with a regal drive. Gets the front foot out of the way and belts it to the left of diving mid-off
backs away to meet a short ball, thwacks it to sweeper cover
slider on middle, backs away, and cuts straight to short extra cover
pitched outside leg and breaks away further. drifting down leg, wide called by ump Brathwaite
Samuels skips out, collapses his back leg and goes inside out in the air, between extra cover and mid-off. Lofted the offbreak with authority
straighter one, defended with bat and pad close together
turn and bounce! Samuels goes back and gets an inside edge that does not carry to short leg
dangled up on middle, Samuels inches forward and defends
tucks this flat ball off the hips to fine leg
Samuels greets Faulkner with a smeared four! Short on off, fraction short, rocks back and pummels to the wide long-on fence
Faulkner drags his length back on off, Samuels cuts a single to sweeper cover. Faulkner collapses in his followthrough. He's fine
overpitched and outside off, forward and creamed to short extra cover
Faulkner rollls his fingers across this legcutter outside off, kicks up from the back of the hand and beats Bravo
another back of the hand legbreak, Bravo swings early and misses
full cutter on off, 110ks, Bravo waited and eased through the covers
flighted legbreak, glanced off the pad behind square

another perfectly pitched legbreak leaves Samuels outside off, he plays back after having ventured forward and edges a cut... It rolls between slip and Smith, stretching his left hand out at lone slip
flatter legbreak outside off, guided to short third man
short and quick on off, backs away and punches to sweeper cover

ump Brathwaite's finger goes up and Bravo walks off. Zampa returns and strikes. Tosses a legbreak, grips in the surface and bounces. Bravo pushes with hard hands and gloves it. Wade forward and to his right to snaffle the tickle
darted short on middle, swat-pulled to deep midwicket
short on off, defended towards point. Ramdin looks for one but is sent back
Faulker goes wide of the crease and cuts it in at 116ks from round the stumps, flicked to midwicket
full and on off, pushed back to the bowler
little cutter outside off, sliced to deep point
full and outside off, offcutter, Samuels glides it fine of short third man for four and his fifty
back of the hand legbreak, swerves in and catches the thigh pad. Rolls to the leg side. Faulkner found extra bounce, again
loopy legbreak outside off, slapped to short extra cover
shorter legbreak, played off the back foot to backward point. Faulkner throws and Zampa misses, giving a single
lobbed up slower and outside off, sharp legbreak, left alone
chopped from off stump through point
quicker legbreak outside off, Samuels plays it late. Dabs a cut to third man, beating backward point to his left. Top shot
tapped to midwicket off the back foot
full and cuts in on off, Ramdin seeks to drive and gets an inside edge to the leg side
back of a length and swings in, bounces over the stumps as Samuels swipes and does not connect. Reverse for NCN?
short on top of off, Samuels gets on top of the bounce and cuts to backward point
another rising short ball, he can't get on top. Chopped to the same fielder
width and Samuels lays into it. He waited for the bad ball. Short and outside off, crunched a cut to the right of backward point. This is a fine knock from Samuels
NCN responds with a 102ks slower bouncer, Samuels half-sways and half-ducks out of the way
flight and deposited over the long-on boundary. Just a hint of air on off, Ramdin backs away by clearing his front foot, opens up the field and slog-sweeps over long-on
slightly short and wide, Ramdin gets on top of the bounce and slaps to cover
goes over mid-on again, against the turn. Flight on off and middle, Ramdin offers more of a straight bat face this time, just a couple
tossed up on off, pushed to cover
more flight on middle and leg, Ramdin defends
flat and wide outside off, thrashed to deep point
some inswing on off. Ramdin looked to drive through cover but it squirts off the inside half to square leg
poor shot but he gets away with it. Clears his front leg, tries to go over mid-off but the ball skews off the outside half and lands in front of sweeper cover
shortish and wide, glided to third man for one
slapped to deep cover off the back foot
loads of extra runs. Inward movement but this one starts too straight and goes further down leg. Bounces in front of Wade and goes away for five.
full and wide outside off, miscued to mid-on
full and straight, jags back in but not as much as it was in the previous game. Blocked solidly to mid-on
full, wide and hammered. Samuels clears his front foot again and thrashes a cover drive. Sweeper cover scurries across to field
back of a length on middle and leg, Ramdin smothers the ball into his pad flap. Picks up the ball and gives it to the bowler
good length on off, chopped to point
tails back in from outside off, steered to third man. That shot should be put away with this movement

short and wide, Samuels backs away and looks to scythe it away but misses. Or did he? Smith wants to review. He has missed it by a substantial distance. Was a hardly audible sound, which probably prompted Smith's call. But all's well for Samuels because there is no bat
shortish length on off, Samuels laces his cut but finds backward point this time
full on middle and leg, tails back in and strikes Ramdin in front. Sliding down leg though
this one has started too straight and gone down leg
slides down leg again, worked off his pads to wide fine leg for a brace. NCN has got to start this wider outside off
slow, short one outside off is dabbed to third man to get one
full toss on off, looking for that yorker but misses. Slashed to deep point. Samuels' pads are almost never in line to the seamers
good length on off, tapped to point for a run, 135 kph

back of a length down leg, nurdled to short fine leg for a run. The throw ricochets off Ramdin's pads to the sweeper cover and the crowd go up in raucous amazement that the batsmen aren't considering the overthrow
it's working though. A leg-stump guard, his pads are well down leg. Hazlweood's inwinger hits Samuels but down leg
full and straight, Samuels chops one back to the bowler. Interesting that Samuels is persistently looking to hit through the off side. With this angle, the leg side seems a higher percentage option
ooh, just wide of midwicket. Full and tailing back in towards off and middle, Samuels tries to go over cover but skews to wide long-on
looks to go straighter this time but that angle helps a squirt off the inside half to long-on
drifting down leg. Better option from Ramdin as he clips to deep square leg
smeared to midwicket for one. Samuels trying to do too much
short and wide, Samuels tries to go through point but the ball skews back to the bowler. Has lost all his shape and timing
again. Shortish delivery on middle, Samuels tries to go through the off side but inside-edges to fine leg. Two a result
slow legcutter outside off, so wide that it would have been called ad Samuels let it go but he reaches out for it to slap to sweeper
full and straight, pushed to midwicket
drifting down leg, whipped towards backward square leg where Khawaja gets around from fine leg to save the boundary with a dive
full and straight to finish, worked to midwicket

six. Very risky stroke and he gets away with it. Flight on off, Samuels comes down and miscues his lofted drive off the outside half. It hangs in the air for a while., Head at long-off backtracks and takes the catch but is falling over. He tries to push it back as he falls over but pushes it over the boundary instead
six more. More flight on off, Samuels runs down and lofts it with the spin, Though he could clear long-ff and he did easily
make that three in a row. More flight outside off, Samuels steps out and hits it in the same area. Clears long-off again, awesome hitting

and he's gone. What is happening? Zampa bowls this flat and quick down leg, Samuels goes back and allows the ball to hit his pad and he goes through for a leg bye. Wade runs across to short square leg, picks up, turns around and throws the stumps down while moving, at the bowler's end. Wow, what an effort from Wadey.
flat on leg, Ramdin is struck on the pad and there is a massive appeal. Pad before bat, struck him in front of leg but where did that pitch?
flat on off, Ramdin defends
yorker on off, Pollard steps out and pushes to mid-on
full on off, Pollard shimmies down again, trying to get ahead of the swing. Drives back to the bowler who throws back but misses
back of a length on off, Pollard gets on top of the bounce and defends
shortish delivery on off, inside-edged onto his huge frame
shortish outside off, drag-pulled to deep square leg
overpitched on off, smeared to fine leg
flight outside off, good length. Ramdin leaves
more flight on off, driven back to the bowler
shorter length on middle, shovelled to midwicket
shortish and wide, slashed to deep point
flat on middle and leg, pushed to midwicket

phew. That is ridiculous. Unbelievable. Nonsense. What? Tossed up outside off, Pollard tried to go over long-on by dragging it but got more of a leading edge which flies over cover. And went a fair way back too. A 90 degree change in shot direction, still enough muscle behind it.
strays down leg for a wide
whipped past square leg this time and there is no deep fielder so WI inch closer. Looking for that inswinger but too straight again

that is probably where NCN should have been from the start. Bowls the offcutter slightly wider outside off, and Ramdin wants to guide to third man but doesn't account for prodigious movement back into him. Goes right in the gap between bat and pad and clatters into off stump
full on off, good line that. Driven to cover

gone. Holder is given. But he opts for the review. Good length delivery outside off, which jags back in again. Holder attempts a big swing and the ball goes through between bat and pad. Looks like he has missed it, but there is a sound. Not sure what it is. Swerves back in and Wade collects well, diving to his left. Not enough evidence to overturn this apparently, and Holder cannot believe it. Hangs on his bat before trudging off ever so slowly. Would have stayed not out had he been given not out. On replays, looks like there is a big deviation as the ball passes the bat, so good decision
yorker on off, blocked
honing in on that off stump but Brathwaite's bat intervenes. Much better over from NCN
back of a length on middle, Pollard shimmies and works to square leg
good length on off, tapped to point
fullish on off, steered to point
opens the bat face to get this one tho third man
shortish and wide, Pollard tries to get on top of the bounce but cannot. Goes through with his cut and gets it past point, races away
smashed over midwicket for three. Ran down to the pitch and flicked it away to bring WI closer
short and wide, Pollard has a loose waft but misses
full and wide outside off, Pollard tries to clear midwicket again but toe-ends to third man
shortish on off, defended by his feet
that is it. Short and wide, steered past point as WI post a four-wicket win to beat Australia
